{
  "stem": "10549.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You could not leave the city.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were restricted only to, to the city where we were.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And right away, they made all kind of restriction.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we just stayed where we were, and we couldn't go out there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I found out later on that my sister went to Russia, because right after the war broke out with, between Germany and Russia, she went to Russia, where she lived through in Russia.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not exactly.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I got the news that some people who knew something about her, that she was killed in the city where, when they're, where liquidating the Jewish population of that city, that she got killed in that city.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was Borisoff.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, that was more to the Russian border on the-- it was still on the Polish side.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We stayed for around three, four months.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my father decided-- he had some jewelry with him, and he tried to make a, a living.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's how we-- he couldn't work.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we tried to go to a larger city, you know, in order to maybe sell some of his belongings.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he went to city of Cracow-- 'Cracoff' Polish-- in 'Cracoff'.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But it's Cracow.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he was supposed to come back, but he never came back.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "After three, four weeks I didn't hear from him, so I decide-- I was smuggling myself on the train that time, and I decided to go to the same city.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I found out that, unfortunately, he was picked up on a raid, because the Germans used to make raids on the Jewish sections.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Certain sections they made the raids, and they went from house to house, and they used to confiscate a lot of things.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And, and they caught my father, also on that raid, with that jewelry.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They confiscate the jewelry.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they, they locked him in, in a, in a prison.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And that's how I found out that he was in a prison.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I tried to [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] do all my best in order to release him from the prison, but I was not successful.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And one day-- my father was a very-- his hobby used to be listen to operas.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He had a radio and listen to it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He was-- he liked music.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And one day, early in the morning, I went in front of the prison, and I knew that one of those windows were facing the street.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I couldn't holler in order for him to, to, to see me, but I whistled his favorite tune.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And was very quiet.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And he came over to the window.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I had a chance to, to, to say a few words to him.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And fortunately, after two weeks later, they released him from the prison.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And we lived in Cracow for few months until every, all the Jews had to go to, go to ghetto.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And they, they made all the Jewish population-- all the Jewish people had to go to Jewish ghetto.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Cracow ghetto.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Cracow ghetto.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was very cramped, very cramped.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I can imagine that-- I don't know how many thousands of Jews used to live in a big sections, and all of a sudden the whole ghetto was maybe [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] five or six blocks versus a, a half a city, because Cracow had a big Jewish population.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a big Jewish population.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't know exactly how many thousands of Jews were there, but there was-- I don't know if it was 50,000 or 70,000.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But it was very cramped.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I don't remember how many thousand people.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But it was very cramped conditions.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Fortunately, for me and my father that I'm-- on one occasion, where we had to-- it was before we went to ghetto-- we had to register to-- every Jewish person had to register, to go to [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] labor, labor office, like.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the Germans used to come, come to the labor office, and they used to request so many Jewish workers for their purpose, whatever purpose it was, to clean the facility, to wash or to carry coal or to carry furniture or whatever it was.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And one time I was picked up by [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] the German Gestapo headquarters, whoever it was.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we worked on the Gestapo headquarters as a laborer.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I was carrying coal.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I was carrying furniture because the Gestapo were in charge of liquidating and confiscating all the wealth or whatever they were taking away from everybody, and mostly Jewish population.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So I become one of the workers.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And because I became a useful person-- when the ghetto started in Cracow, they designated one building for their workers.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
